# üß† BASIC CONCEPTS

## üßæ What is Vim?


# Vim is a highly configurable text editor built to enable efficient text editing. It‚Äôs an improved version of the older vi editor.

üõ† Vim Modes


Vim operates in modes, not just insert like most editors:

Normal mode (Esc): Navigate and manipulate text.

Insert mode (i): Type text.

Visual mode (v): Select text.

Command-line mode (:): Run commands like :w, :q, etc.

Replace mode (R): Overwrites characters.


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚å®Ô∏è BASIC COMMANDS

Action	Command

Save	:w

Quit	:q

Save and Quit	:wq or ZZ

Quit without saving	:q!

Open file	vim filename

Save as (write to new file)	:w newname.txt


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üöÄ INSERT MODE SHORTCUTS
Enter insert mode using:

i ‚Üí insert before cursor

I ‚Üí insert at beginning of line

a ‚Üí append after cursor

A ‚Üí append at end of line

o ‚Üí open new line below

O ‚Üí open new line above


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üì¶ NORMAL MODE COMMANDS


üìçNavigation

Action	Command

Move left/right	h, l

Move up/down	k, j

Next/previous word	w, b

End of word	e

Start of line	0

First non-blank char	^

End of line	$

Go to line n	:n

Go to last line	G

Go to top	gg

Half page up/down	Ctrl+u, Ctrl+d

Full page up/down	Ctrl+b, Ctrl+f


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
## üìù Editing Text
Action	Command

Delete character	x

Delete word	dw

Delete line	dd

Copy line	yy

Paste	p

Undo	u

Redo	Ctrl+r

Replace character	r<char>

Replace mode	R

Change word	cw

Change line	cc


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## üîç SEARCHING & REPLACING
üîé Search
/text ‚Üí Search forward for "text"

?text ‚Üí Search backward

n ‚Üí next match

N ‚Üí previous match

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


## üîÅ Replace
:s/old/new/ ‚Üí Replace first "old" in current line

:s/old/new/g ‚Üí Replace all in line

:%s/old/new/g ‚Üí Replace all in file

:%s/old/new/gc ‚Üí Confirm before each


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


# üìè VISUAL MODE

## Mode	Action

v	start character selection

V	start line selection

Ctrl+v	block/column selection

